Name: ALTITUDE IN METRES
Explanation: THE VERTICAL DISTANCE IN METRES ABOVE MEAN SEA LEVEL (MSL) OF AN AIRBORNE OBJECT, LEVEL, OR POINT.

Name: MINIMUM ALTITUDE IN METRES
Explanation: THE MINUMUM ALTITUDE TO WHICH AN AIRSPACE COORDINATION AREA (ACA) EXTENDS.

Name: MAXIMUM ALTITUDE IN METRES
Explanation: THE MAXIMUM ALTITUDE TO WHICH AN AIRSPACE COORDINATION AREA (ACA) EXTENDS.
